@Mike

You might forge yourself a new line of work.

Like finding a needle in a haystack.

@john ezra
I can't see how you could call this new font Courier Bold. To my aging eyes, the font is lighter and harder to read, though what I'm typing now seems the same as before. Also, the Recommend is all the way over to the right, forcing me to crane my neck to see it. Worst of all, I can't figure out whether replies are showing or not, and when I click on them, the whole response column jumps like crazy and I lose whatever I was looking at. (I'm on a browser on my PC).

It was already broken, but as the old saying goes, "If it ain't broke, don't fix it." In this case, it's broken, so don't make it worse. The adults have left the room.

@Stuart
You're misreading ipconfig. It's not IP-config. It's IPC on Fig. This special command will instruct your 3D printer to create a très chic French appetizer consisting of a sauce of Ikra, Pimentoes, and Coffee drizzled on sliced figs.
Of course, it's still composed of plastic microbeads, so it's about as tasty as the theoretical original.

@Grumpy
I hear people refer to Internet Protocol Addresses as IPs all the time. Probably more commonly than someone would bother to say IP address.
Maybe it's a Gen X thing.

@Andrzej

We have veered way off topic, but as long as we're here: anyone who liked Better Call Saul and has deprived themselves of Breaking Bad has missed one of the best TV series ever made.  They are the halves of a superb whole, each making the other a richer viewing experience. 

I smiled reading that you "never heard or read ( anything) about" BB that would make you like it: what on earth could one read about BCS that makes it sound likable?  Torture in the desert?  A senile man self immolating?  Both series deal with despicable behavior in very intertwined, complicated scenarios that rivet attention and totally captivate.  Andrzej, it's one of the best series you have never seen.  Do yourself a favor, watch!

